AUDIO: 'In this video, I\'m going to show you how to get this 3D viewport aesthetic and I just came up with this. So, feel free to steal it in your next edit if you think this looks cool. But anyway, let me show you exactly how I made this. I\'m in After Effects and as you can see I have this clip loaded up and what we\'re'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'essentially going to want to start with is by screenshotting our footage. So, make sure you find frames where you can see all the elements that are in the frame, but also the frame that has the least motion blur. So,'

